# API Conventions

- `apps/api/src/index.ts` is the Express entrypoint.
- tRPC routers are composed in `apps/api/src/trpc/router.ts`.
- Module routers live under `apps/api/src/modules/*/router.ts`.
- Auth and request context logic live under `apps/api/src/auth`.

- When adding API behavior:
- prefer putting endpoints in the appropriate module router
- prefer putting individual functions in modules/{moduke}/services
- keep auth and role checks aligned with tRPC procedures and request context
- reuse existing module and service structure before creating new top-level folders

- If API code needs database tables, import shared schema from `@db/schema` rather than redefining shapes locally.
